KEY: gutierrez2024hipporag
BIBTEX:
@article{gutierrez2024hipporag,
  title={HippoRAG: Neurobiologically Inspired Long-Term Memory for Large Language Models},
  author={Guti{\'e}rrez, Bernal Jim{\'e}nez and Shu, Yiheng and Gu, Yu and Yasunaga, Michihiro and Su, Yu},
  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2405.14831},
  year={2024},
  url={https://arxiv.org/abs/2405.14831}
}
CLAIM_1: HippoRAG uses Personalized PageRank (PPR) on knowledge graphs to perform single-step multi-hop retrieval, compressing multiple retrieval hops into one operation by leveraging graph connectivity to find relevant paths across documents.
CLAIM_2: Compared to iterative retrieval methods like IRCoT, HippoRAG achieves comparable or better performance while being 10-30 times cheaper and 6-13 times faster, demonstrating 20% improvement over state-of-the-art methods on multi-hop question answering.

