  journal={IEEE Transactions on Knowledge and Data Engineering},
  volume={36},
  number={7},
  pages={3580--3599},
  year={2024},
  publisher={IEEE},
  doi={10.1109/TKDE.2024.3352100}
}
CLAIM_1: Proposes a comprehensive taxonomy of KG+LLM integration methods organized into three frameworks: KG-enhanced LLMs (incorporating KGs during pre-training/inference), LLM-augmented KGs (using LLMs for KG tasks), and Synergized LLMs+KGs (bidirectional reasoning).
CLAIM_2: Identifies that structured knowledge from KGs can enhance LLMs' factual accuracy and interpretability, while LLMs can help with KG construction, completion, and text generation, creating a mutually beneficial ecosystem.

