}
CLAIM_1: Provides a systematic taxonomy of graph retrieval strategies in RAG, categorizing them into graph-based indexing, graph-guided retrieval, and graph-enhanced generation, with specific algorithms for each stage.
CLAIM_2: Identifies key failure modes including semantic mishits (retrieving unrelated but similar content), context fragmentation (missing connections between related documents), and scalability challenges with large knowledge graphs.

